    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1432" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄ̄ρητος</span></b> : doubtful word,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wished-for</span> (if from <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀ̄ράομαι</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄ̄ρητον δὲ τοκεῦσι γόον
            καὶ πένθος ἔθηκας</span>, ‘hast awakened the desire of
          lamentation’ (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵ̄μερος γόου</span>), <i><span class="en">Il. 17.37</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            24.741</span></i>; according to others, for <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄρρητος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥηθῆναι</span>),
          ‘unspeakable.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
